(42, 7, 25, 11, 10, 5, 5, 'a man clothed in soft raiment', 'Connection of Apparel and Status', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of clothing and status. Luke contrasts the soft raiment of the elite with the humble nature of John the Baptist, while 1 Kings describes the elaborate apparel of servants in a royal setting.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
