(42, 7, 25, 17, 1, 11, 11, 'gorgeously apparelled, and live delicately', 'Connection of Royal Presentation', 'Both passages emphasize the presentation of beauty and status. In Luke, the focus is on those in fine clothing, while Esther highlights Vashti''s beauty as a display for the king and his court.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 25, 23, 59, 17, 17, 'soft raiment', 'Connection of Clothing Imagery', 'This connection highlights the theme of clothing as a symbol of one''s character and purpose. Both passages use garments to convey deeper meanings: Luke contrasts soft raiment with the strength of righteousness and zeal in Isaiah.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 25, 40, 6, 29, 29, 'gorgeously apparelled', 'Connection of Clothing and Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of clothing and its relation to status. Both passages emphasize that those who are gorgeously apparelled, like Solomon, do not compare to the simplicity and beauty found in God''s creation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 25, 12, 1, 8, 8, 'a man clothed in soft raiment', 'Contrast of Clothing and Lifestyle', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the luxurious attire of those in power and the humble appearance of Elijah. Both passages emphasize the significance of outward appearance in relation to one''s true character and calling.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 26, 42, 1, 76, 76, 'a prophet? Yea, I say unto you', 'Connection of Prophetic Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a prophet. Luke 1:76 identifies John as a prophet preparing the way, while Luke 7:26 affirms the significance of prophets, suggesting a deeper prophetic mission.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 26, 42, 20, 6, 6, 'a prophet? Yea, I say unto you', 'Connection of Prophetic Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of John as a prophet. In Luke 7:26, Jesus affirms John''s prophetic role, while Luke 20:6 reflects the people''s belief in his prophetic status.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 26, 43, 5, 35, 35, 'much more than a prophet', 'Connection of Light and Prophecy', 'This connection highlights the role of John the Baptist as a significant figure in both passages. Luke refers to him as ''much more than a prophet,'' while John describes him as ''a burning and a shining light,'' emphasizing his prophetic and illuminating nature.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 26, 40, 11, 9, 14, 'a prophet? Yea, I say unto you, and much more than a prophet.', 'Connection Between John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize John the Baptist''s role as a prophet and messenger. They highlight his significance in relation to the kingdom of heaven and the fulfillment of prophecy.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 26, 43, 3, 26, 30, 'a prophet? Yea, I say unto you', 'John''s Role as a Prophet', 'Both passages emphasize the prophetic role of John the Baptist. In Luke, he is recognized as ''much more than a prophet,'' while in John, he clarifies his role as the one sent before Christ, highlighting his purpose in relation to the bridegroom.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 27, 39, 3, 1, 1, 'my messenger before thy face', 'Connection of Messengers', 'This connection highlights the role of the messenger in both passages. Both Luke 7:27 and Malachi 3:1 emphasize the theme of preparing the way before the Lord.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 27, 42, 1, 76, 76, 'prepare thy way before thee', 'Connection of Prophetic Preparation', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a messenger who prepares the way for the Lord. They highlight the theme of going before the face of the Lord to prepare his ways.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 27, 41, 1, 2, 2, 'my messenger before thy face', 'Connection of Messengers in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a messenger who prepares the way. The exact phrase ''my messenger before thy face'' links the two texts, highlighting their shared theme of preparation.', 'quotation', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 27, 39, 4, 5, 6, 'my messenger before thy face', 'Connection of Messengers', 'This connection highlights the theme of a messenger sent to prepare the way. Both passages emphasize the role of a prophet, with Luke referencing the prophecy in Malachi about sending Elijah.', 'prophecy', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 27, 40, 11, 10, 10, 'Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee.', 'Connection of Messenger Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a messenger who prepares the way. The identical wording highlights the prophetic nature of this figure in relation to Jesus.', 'quotation', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 27, 42, 1, 15, 17, 'prepare thy way before thee', 'Preparation for the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a messenger who prepares the way for the Lord. Luke 7:27 quotes the prophecy about this messenger, while Luke 1:15-17 describes the specific mission of John the Baptist to turn hearts and make ready a people.', 'prophecy', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 27, 43, 1, 23, 23, 'prepare thy way before thee', 'Connection of Messengers', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a messenger preparing the way for the Lord. Luke refers to a messenger sent before, while John identifies himself as the voice crying in the wilderness, echoing this preparatory theme.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 28, 40, 11, 11, 11, 'there is not a greater prophet than John the Baptist', 'John the Baptist''s Greatness', 'Both passages emphasize that among those born of women, John the Baptist is the greatest prophet. They also highlight that the least in the kingdom of God is greater than him, suggesting a significant shift in status within the kingdom.', 'parallel', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 28, 40, 13, 16, 17, 'greater than he', 'Prophetic Significance of John the Baptist', 'This connection highlights the significance of prophetic insight. Both passages emphasize the unique privilege of those who witness and hear the message of God, contrasting them with earlier prophets who longed for such revelations.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 28, 51, 1, 25, 27, 'greater than he', 'Prophetic Role and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the transition from John the Baptist, the greatest prophet, to the revelation of Christ among the Gentiles. Both passages emphasize the unfolding of God''s plan and the significance of Christ in the lives of believers.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 28, 58, 11, 39, 40, 'greater than he', 'Prophetic Significance of Faith', 'This connection highlights the significance of faith in both passages. John the Baptist is recognized as the greatest prophet, yet those in the kingdom of God are deemed greater, emphasizing a new covenant of faith that surpasses previous promises.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 28, 42, 9, 48, 48, 'he that is least in the kingdom of God', 'Greatness in the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of greatness in the kingdom of God. They highlight that being ''least'' in the kingdom is a position of honor, contrasting with the greatness of John the Baptist.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 28, 42, 10, 23, 24, 'not a greater prophet than John the Baptist', 'Prophetic Significance of John', 'This connection highlights the significance of John the Baptist as the greatest prophet, while also emphasizing the unique privilege of the disciples to witness and hear the teachings of Jesus. Both passages reflect on the value of prophetic insight and the blessings of revelation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 28, 49, 3, 8, 9, 'least in the kingdom of God', 'Greatness in the Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of humility and greatness in the kingdom of God. Both passages emphasize the idea that those considered least, like John the Baptist and Paul, hold significant roles in God''s plan.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
