(42, 7, 29, 42, 7, 35, 35, 'justified God', 'Justification in Wisdom and Baptism', 'This connection highlights the theme of justification in both passages. In Luke 7:29, the people justified God through their acceptance of John''s baptism, while in Luke 7:35, wisdom is justified by her children, suggesting a parallel in the concept of validation through actions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 29, 7, 1, 7, 7, 'justified God', 'Divine Justice and Retribution', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine justice, as both passages reflect on how actions lead to consequences. In Luke, the people justify God through their acceptance of baptism, while in Judges, Adoni-bezek acknowledges God''s retribution for his deeds.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
